title: NEIC, USGS, 7.7 quake in Sumatra to 7.2 quake in Baja California, World, April 06, 2010
name: NEIC, USGS, 7.7 quake in Sumatra to 7.2 quake in Baja California, World, April 06, 2010
description:
The point shapefile shows the locations of all the earthquakes of magnitude 2.5 or more for the U.S.A and 4.5 magnitude or more across the globe. Temporally, these include the two big quakes, 7.2 in Baja California on 4th April and 7.7 quake in Sumatra on 6th April. Sumatra had two after shocks of 5.4 and 5.1 nearby in the Southwest direction. All of these struck at the depth of between 31 Km and 35 Km. Thus even though the 7.7 magnitude Sumatra quake is much larger than 7.2 Baja California quake, the depth for Baja was much shallower than Sumatra. One cause for worry is that Sumatra quake was off-shore and thus raising the possibility of tsunami.
